
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-pwe3-redundancy-09.txt'>
    <title>"Pseudowire Redundancy", Praveen Muley, Mustapha Aissaoui, Matthew Bocci</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-pwe3-redundancy-09.txt</link>
    <description>This document describes a framework comprised of a number of scenarios and associated requirements for pseudowire (PW) redundancy. A set of redundant PWs is configured between provider edge (PE) nodes in single -segment PW applications, or between terminating PE (T-PE) nodes in multi-segment PW applications.  In order for the PE/T-PE nodes to indicate the preferred PW to use for forwarding PW packets to one another, a new PW status is required to indicate the preferential forwarding status of active or standby for each PW in the redundant set.</description>
    <dc:date>2012-06-26T22:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
